**// HTML 'hello world': //**
HTML:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
	<title>Hello world</title>
</head>
<body>
	<h1>Hello World</h1>

</body>
</html>

**// Python 'hello world' //**
 Python:
 print('Hello World')
 
 **// JavaScript 'hello world' //**
 JavaScript:
 <!DOCTYPE HTML>
<html>

<body>

  <script>
    alert( 'Hello, world!' );
  </script>

</body>

</html>

**// Java 'hello world' //**
Java:
class HelloWorld {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Hello, World!"); 
    }
}

**// Modern JS //**

Modern Javascript:

document.write('Hello, world!')

**// jQuery //**
jQuery:

$("body").append("Hello world!");

**// Append function in jQuery can have other names too //**

**// MatLab //**
MatLab:

disp('Hello, world!')

**// Ruby //**
Ruby:
puts "Hello, World"
